# Always create a verified GitHub Release

After any user-facing Exo change, ship a **real GitHub Release** before finishing.

A git tag alone is NOT a release. The download uses:
`GET https://api.github.com/repos/ImAvgErix/Exo/releases/latest`

## Required steps

1. Bump `VERSION` and `Exo/Exo.csproj` `<Version>` (and kit `VERSION` when scripts change).
2. Commit and push to `main`.
3. Run `.\Release-Exo.ps1`.
4. **Verify the Release (not the tag)** with:
   ```powershell
   (Invoke-RestMethod https://api.github.com/repos/ImAvgErix/Exo/releases/latest).tag_name
   (Invoke-RestMethod https://api.github.com/repos/ImAvgErix/Exo/releases/latest).assets.name
   ```
   Must equal the new version and include **`Exo.exe` only** (no zip required).
5. Tell the user the release URL and direct exe download:
   `https://github.com/ImAvgErix/Exo/releases/latest/download/Exo.exe`

## Do not

- Treat `gh release create` success or a pushed tag as done without API `/releases/latest` verification
- Finish after commit/push only
- Leave an older release marked Latest
- Ship zip-only releases; the primary asset is double-click **Exo.exe**
